dxf2svg
Class DxfConverter

java.lang.Object
  dxf2svg.DxfConverter
public final class DxfConverter
extends java.lang.Object

This class actually coordinates the building of the SVG graphic. It is an intermediary between DxfParser and SvgBuilder. It gets the Vector data from the Parser and creates the rest of the objects needed to finish the conversion, namely the Processors, StyleSheetGenerator and SvgBuilder.

Version:
1.52 - February 14, 2005
Author:
Andrew Nisbet

DxfConverter

public DxfConverter(java.lang.String path)
The coordination of the production of SVG graphics is done within this class. This class encapsulates vectors of the 7 different parts of a DXF file and hands them off to the appropriate Processor objects.

getFileName

public java.lang.String getFileName()
This method allows any object to query the current conversion file name. This is useful for objects like AnimationEngine which is persistant to all files during the conversion but needs to flag a file by name to the logger object.

getFilePath

public java.lang.String getFilePath()
This method allows any object to query the current conversion file path. This is useful for objects like DxfImageObjectReference which uses it to find raster images for embedding into the SVG.

addHatchPattern

public void addHatchPattern(SvgHatch hatch,
                            SvgHatchPattern pattern)
This method allows a hatch pattern definition to be added to the list of other objects to be output in the <defs> section of the SVG file (along with symbols). Duplicate hatch patterns are searched for to optimize the database of patterns, and patterns that have the same name but different data are renamed to avoid name conflicts in the SVG file.

getImageObjectReference

public DxfImageObjectReference getImageObjectReference(java.lang.String imageHandle)
Used by SvgImage to get a reference to its specific image handle (dxf hex code handle). The handle is used by the SvgImage to locate individual images (if there are more than one) so that it can base64 encode the image into the SVG.

getStyleSheetGenerator

public StyleSheetGenerator getStyleSheetGenerator()
This method returns the StyleSheetGenerator currently being used by this thread. It is mainly used SvgObjects, in their constructors, to allow them to determine the current Thread's StyleSheetGenerator.

Returns:
StyleSheetGenerator.

SvgUtil This object encapsulates all the Dxf conversion utilities.
